JWT = JSON Web Token (RFC 7519)
Stateless, compact, self-contained token for transmitting claims.

STRUCTURE:
  header.payload.signature
  eyJhbGci.eyJzdWIi.SflKxwRJS

  Header: { "alg": "HS256", "typ": "JWT" }
  Payload: { "sub": "user42", "roles": ["USER"], "exp": 1735689600, "iat": 1735686000 }
  Signature: HMACSHA256(base64(header) + '.' + base64(payload), secret)

DEFAULT JWT CONFIG WITH SPRING SECURITY:
  // Dependencies: spring-security-oauth2-jose or io.jsonwebtoken:jjwt
  // Generate token on login
  public String generateToken(UserDetails user) {
    return Jwts.builder()
      .setSubject(user.getUsername())
      .setIssuedAt(new Date())
      .setExpiration(new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + 86400000)) // 24hrs
      .signWith(secretKey, SignatureAlgorithm.HS256)
      .compact();
  }

CUSTOM JWT CONFIG:
  // Store roles in claims
  .claim("roles", user.getAuthorities().stream().map(GrantedAuthority::getAuthority).toList())

  // Validate token
  Claims claims = Jwts.parserBuilder()
    .setSigningKey(secretKey).build()
    .parseClaimsJws(token).getBody();
  String username = claims.getSubject();

ADDING LOGIN ROUTE:
  @PostMapping("/api/auth/login")
  public ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> login(@RequestBody LoginRequest req) {
    authManager.authenticate(new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken(req.username(), req.password()));
    String token = jwtService.generateToken(req.username());
    return ResponseEntity.ok(Map.of("token", token));
  }

JWT FILTER:
  @Component
  public class JwtAuthFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
    protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res, FilterChain chain) {
      String header = req.getHeader("Authorization");
      if (header != null && header.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
        String token = header.substring(7);
        String username = jwtService.extractUsername(token);
        // set SecurityContext authentication
      }
      chain.doFilter(req, res);
    }
  }

SECURITY CONFIG:
  Add JWT filter before UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter
  .sessionManagement().sessionCreationPolicy(STATELESS)
  Permit /api/auth/** without authentication
  Require authentication for all other routes

Instructor-led session — Duration: 5 Hours
Faculty: Dr. ALOK CHAUHAN

JUNIT 5 INTRODUCTION:
  JUnit = standard testing framework for Java
  Annotations:
    @Test           — marks a test method
    @BeforeEach     — runs before each test
    @AfterEach      — runs after each test
    @BeforeAll      — once before all tests (static)
    @AfterAll       — once after all tests (static)
    @Disabled       — skip this test
    @ParameterizedTest + @ValueSource — run test with multiple inputs

  // Example
  class UserServiceTest {
    @Test
    void shouldReturnUserById() {
      User user = userService.findById(1L);
      assertNotNull(user);
      assertEquals("Alice", user.getName());
    }

    @Test
    void shouldThrowWhenNotFound() {
      assertThrows(UserNotFoundException.class, () -> userService.findById(999L));
    }
  }

ASSERTIONS:
  assertEquals(expected, actual)
  assertNotNull(object)
  assertTrue(condition)
  assertThrows(ExceptionClass.class, () -> method())
  assertAll("group", () -> assertEquals(..), () -> assertTrue(..))

MOCKITO:
  Mockito creates mock objects (fake implementations) for dependencies.

  @ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
  class UserServiceTest {
    @Mock UserRepository userRepo;     // fake repository
    @InjectMocks UserService service;  // inject mocks into service

    @Test
    void testCreateUser() {
      UserDto dto = new UserDto("Alice", 25);
      User saved = new User(1L, "Alice", 25);

      when(userRepo.save(any(User.class))).thenReturn(saved);

      User result = service.create(dto);

      verify(userRepo, times(1)).save(any());  // verify call happened
      assertEquals("Alice", result.getName());
    }

    @Test
    void testFindById_NotFound() {
      when(userRepo.findById(999L)).thenReturn(Optional.empty());
      assertThrows(UserNotFoundException.class, () -> service.findById(999L));
    }
  }

MOCKITO METHODS:
  when(...).thenReturn(value)       — stub return value
  when(...).thenThrow(exception)    — stub exception
  verify(mock, times(n)).method()   — verify interaction
  verify(mock, never()).method()    — verify NOT called
  ArgumentCaptor — capture argument passed to mock

SPRING BOOT TESTING:
  @SpringBootTest — full integration test (loads all beans)
  @WebMvcTest(UserController.class) — only controller layer (fast)
  @DataJpaTest    — only JPA layer, in-memory H2 database
  @MockBean       — Spring-aware mock (replaces bean in context)
